<subSubSection id="6D837C85103DFFA2DBE2FDE6497F29C6" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="25262F0E103DFFA2DBE2FDE6497F29C6" blockId="24.[151,1437,151,747]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103DFFA2DBE2FDE64D0129EA" bold="true" box="[199,308,685,711]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Remarks</emphasis>
. In colour, 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103DFFA2DA90FDE64E1529EA" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[437,544,685,711]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilis">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103DFFA2DA90FDE64E1529EA" box="[437,544,685,711]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A. nobilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103DFFA2D9BAFDE64F3A29EA" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[671,783,685,711]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallens">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103DFFA2D9BAFDE64F3A29EA" box="[671,783,685,711]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A. pallens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
newly described below from 
<collectingCountry id="5D8E6F9E103DFFA2DF78FDE6488629EA" box="[1117,1203,685,711]" name="Taiwan" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103DFFA2DE14FDE649A929EA" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[1329,1436,685,711]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilis">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103DFFA2DE14FDE649A929EA" box="[1329,1436,685,711]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A. nobilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the mesopresternum and mesoeusternum narrowly fused, whereas these are broadly fused in 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103DFFA2DFF6FD9A497629C6" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[1235,1347,721,747]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallens">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103DFFA2DFF6FD9A497629C6" box="[1235,1347,721,747]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A. pallens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
